text: On the latest #TWiV we review @MichaelWorobey  dissection of the early #COVID19 cases in Wuhan, and the discovery that herpesviruses assimilate cellular kinesin to produce motorized virus particles https://t.co/DIpx80X4yM https://t.co/PaABanLdhh

In #COVID19 clinical update Dr. Griffin on 25% of US cases in children, reinfection and presence of antibodies, national surveillance for acute flaccid myelitis in US, monoclonal antibody treatment of infection in vaccinated, high-risk individuals https://t.co/W6I5P5imfY https://t.co/6KxgOAACyq

How #SARSCoV2 attacks the olfactory mucosa but spares the olfactory bulb, vaccination with BNT162b2 induces virus-specific stem cell memory T cells, and development of an oral protease inhibitor for the treatment of #COVID19 https://t.co/evbHyMZQQ8 https://t.co/NetFJ11GOE

In his weekly #COVID19 clinical update Dr. Griffin on vaccine protection among US veterans, absence of long COVID in vaccinated/infected, REGEN-COV mAb gives long term protection, Pfizer protease inhibitor 89% effective preventing hospitalization or death https://t.co/Jv2iTE7uQH https://t.co/et2S8uCxCd

Greg Zuckerman joins #TWiV to discuss his book that explores the race to produce #COVID19 vaccines, with insights into the companies, scientists, and executives involved and the rivalries, ambitions, ego, and a desire to save the world https://t.co/fFPZdaLxuL https://t.co/a6740U1oCa
